Description of Features :¶

There are 34 features to describe electrical consumption from 3 different houses and weather dataset :

  1. Date & Time: year-month-day, hour:minute
  2. FurnaceHRV [kW] : energy use
  3. CellarOutlets [kW] : energy use
  4. WashingMachine [kW] : energy use
  5. FridgeRange [kW] : energy use
  6. DisposalDishwasher [kW] : energy use
  7. KitchenLights [kW] : energy use
  8. BedroomOutlets [kW] : energy use
  9. BedroomLights [kW] : energy use
  10. MasterOutlets [kW] : energy use
  11. DuctHeaterHRV [kW] : energy use
  12. use [kW] : energy use of solar panel
  13. gen [kW] : energy generated by solar panel
  14. ElectricRange [kW] : energy use
  15. Dryer [kW] : energy use
  16. GarageMudroomLights [kW] : energy use
  17. DiningRoomOutlets [kW] : energy use
  18. MudroomOutlets : energy use
  19. MasterBathOutlets [kW] : energy use
  20. GarageOutlets [kW] : energy use
  21. BasementOutdoorOutlets [kW] : energy use
  22. Temperature in Fahrenheit
  23. humidity %
  24. Pressure : in mm Hg
  25. Wind speed: in m/s
  26. Visibility : in km
  27. summary: weather condition clear or cloudy
  28. apparentTemperature: feels-like temperature
  29. cloudCover
  30. windBearing
  31. precipIntensity
  32. dewpoint
  33. icon: weather description clear or cloudy with time specified
  34. Total kWh : Total energy used by appliances, in kWh

Preliminary Observations: ¶

  • Meter4_data is having zero values , it shall be removed in order not to affect the model by showing the zero summation step
  • Need to drop some columns in weather dataset such as [icon,summary] due to not having significance, run value counts on summary column before you drop it
  • Need to drop Zero valued columns such as use (kW) & gen (kW) in data of meter 2
  • The datasets shall be merged into one dataset, but before merging, Time observations need to be unifed to "Hourly" basis

Data cleaning ¶

Summary and icon were dropped due to being general and useless because we have the detailed weather features

Pre-Processing : ¶

There is a problem in retreiving data from sensors as some of the sensors maybe corrupt and send false data , those corrupt readings can be indicated as they are considered to be outliers. When I checked the trends for each consumption feedback , I noticed that total energy consumption in 2015 during month of January shows outliers

Steps to be done as follows: 1) To check if outliers exist and remove them accordingly so model is not affected by outliers.
2) to make sure that all the features are withing the same scaleThis method scales by setting the mean of the data to 0, and the standard deviation to 1
3) Subtracts the mean value from feature value, and divides by standard deviation
4) This results in the standardized distribution

a)Train set is the period from february 2015 till september 2016
b)Test set is the period from november 2016 to december 2016
c) the label is KW
d) The features are the weather features , day of week , hour , month and year

K-FOLD cross validation for Ridge regression ¶

In [63]:
# Hyper parameter tunning 
model = Ridge()
# define model evaluation method
cv = RepeatedKFold(n_splits=10, n_repeats=3, random_state=1)
# define grid
grid = dict()
grid['alpha'] = np.arange(0, 10, 0.1)
# define search
search = GridSearchCV(model, grid, scoring='neg_mean_absolute_error', cv=cv, n_jobs=-1)
# perform the search
results = search.fit(X_std, Y)
# summarize
print('MAE: %.3f' % results.best_score_)
print('Config: %s' % results.best_params_)

MAE: -0.333
Config: {'alpha': 0.0}

Prediction Models Conclusion: ¶

1) K-Neighbors regressor is the best for this problem, showing the lowest RMSE among other models used
2) The energy prediction model showed relatively high mean absolute error because energy consumption is not fully dependant on weather features, and might depend on other factors such as people leave the building for vacations, install new equipments , remove old equipment, etc.
